
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dbus-run-session` baraye ejra kardan yek dastoor dar yek `DBus` session jadid be kar miravad. `DBus` yek rah baraye barname-ha ast ke ba ham digar gap bezanand. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ke yek barname ra dar yek mohit izol-shode (isolated) ejra konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`      --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye estefade az dastoor.
    🔹 `--version`   --> ℹ️ Namayesh version e `dbus-run-session`.
    🔹 `--`          --> 🛑 Tamam kardan gozine-ha va shoru kardan dastoor asli.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dbus-run-session gnome-terminal

    🔹 Baz kardan yek terminal `gnome-terminal` dar yek `DBus` session jadid.

    $ dbus-run-session -- firefox

    🔹 Eejad yek `DBus` session jadid va ejra kardan `firefox` dar an.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dbus-run-session xeyes

    🔹 `xeyes` dar yek DBus session jadid ejra mishavad. Agar error dad, ya DBus correctly setup nashode ya barname `xeyes` mojood nist.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dbus-run-session` command is used to run a command in a new `DBus` session. `DBus` is a system for applications to communicate with one another. This command helps you run an application in an isolated environment.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`      --> ❓ Show help about using the command.
    🔹 `--version`   --> ℹ️ Show the version of `dbus-run-session`.
    🔹 `--`          --> 🛑 Signal the end of options and the start of the actual command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dbus-run-session gnome-terminal

    🔹 Open a `gnome-terminal` terminal in a new `DBus` session.

    $ dbus-run-session -- firefox

    🔹 Create a new `DBus` session and run `firefox` within it.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dbus-run-session xeyes

    🔹 `xeyes` runs in a new DBus session. If you get errors, either DBus is not correctly set up, or the `xeyes` program is missing.
